Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pick the @rosemary{10%g}(stalks discarded, leaves roughly chopped) leaves and roughly chop.

Chop @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and half the rosemary.

Toss to coat and spread out. When oven is hot, roast on top shelf, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if needed.

Peel the @garlic{2} cloves. Pop half into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose.

Add the garlic parcel to the tray with the chips to cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press{}).

Season the @pork loin steak{300%g} with salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

== Garlicky Asparagus ==

Trim the bottom of the @asparagus{200%g} and discard.

Place a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once the pan is hot, add the asparagus and remaining garlic and season with salt and pepper.

Fry for ~{1%minute}, then add a splash of @water{to taste} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil.

Cook until tender, ~{4-6%minutes}, then remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

== Garlic Butter ==

Once the garlic has roasted, carefully remove from the foil.

Pop into a #bowl{} and mash with @butter{1%tbsp} (double for 4p) and remaining rosemary.

Season with salt and pepper then mix to combine and set aside.

== Pork and Assembly ==

Return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, fry the pork until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side.

Reduce the heat to medium and fry for an additional ~{4-6%minutes}, turning every 2 mins.

When ~{1%minute} of cooking time remains, add the garlic butter, allow to melt and spoon it over to baste the pork in it.

Once cooked, transfer from the pan, cover and allow to rest, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When everything is ready, thinly slice the pork.

Plate up the butter-basted pork with the chips and asparagus alongside.

Drizzle any remaining buttery juices from the pan over the top.